- load_cable_pos: Load Input Cable (+)
- load_cable_neg: Load Input Cable (−)

Instruction: Reconnect the PSU to the full chain with all switches ON. With respect to PSU Output Cable (−) as reference, measure the voltage at: (1) PSU Output Cable (+); (2) the 12 V/0 V pair at the input of control module 1; (3) between the two cables at the output of each subsequent control module; and (4) the two cables at the load module input. At each point, also check continuity (ohms) between the local + and − lines with power removed. This will determine whether the 1 Ω internal source resistance is simply causing a large voltage drop into a downstream short or miswired module, and will locate where along the series path the effective short or misconnection occurs.
